y lacks skilled workers. Some have even spoken of an "education crisis". These are not abstract concerns. What is occurring in Vietnam's education system today has broad implications for the country’s social, political, economic, and cultural development. Featuring contributions from scholars and policy analysts from within and outside Vietnam, Education in Vietnam addresses key issues pertaining to the political economy of education, the provision and payment for primary and secondary education, and the development of vocational and tertiary education. The book marks an important contribution to existing understandings of Vietnam’s education system and contributes to broader understandings of social conditions and change in contemporary Vietnam.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEducationzVietnamxCongresses. 0aEducation--Vietnam--Congresses. 7aEDUCATION / Organizations & Institutions.2bisacsh1 aChi, Trương Huyền, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobbe, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFatseas, Marea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreire, Alexandre Dormeier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorge, Elizabeth St., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHồng, Nguyễn Minh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiễu, Trần Thị Bích, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLondon, Jonathan D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLondon, Jonathan D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNgọc, Hồ Vũ Khuê, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuyên, Bùi Thái, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabu